✅ What This Command Actually Does
复制代码

openssl s_client -connect example.com:443 -servername example.com
This command acts as a raw TLS client. It performs:
TCP connection to port 443
TLS ClientHello (with SNI = example.com)
TLS handshake
Certificate chain retrieval
Cipher + protocol negotiation
Optional certificate verification (against local trust store)
It prints the full handshake transcript and negotiated session parameters.
✅ What Indicates TLS Handshake Success
You consider TLS successfully established when these elements appear:
1️⃣ Protocol and Cipher Negotiated
Example:
