SSL-Session:
    Protocol  : TLSv1.3
    Cipher    : TLS_AES_256_GCM_SHA384
Meaning:
Handshake finished
Session keys derived
Secure channel ready
This is definitive evidence that TLS handshake completed.
✅ How This Compares to Chrome Security Panel
Chrome Security view shows:
TLS version
Cipher suite
Certificate subject / issuer
Validity dates
SAN names
Trust status
OCSP / revocation
Certificate Transparency
HSTS status
Both Chrome and openssl use the same TLS protocol flow, so negotiated protocol and cipher should match if:
Same hostname (SNI)
Same network path
Same server endpoint
